CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 27, 1946, pg. 16 reads: "'Water Circus' - Another big feature of Frog Week will be the gigantic 'Water Circuis [sic]' at Ammon Pool on the night of Aug. 9. Beautiful girls, crack men swimmers and side-splitting clowns will all cavort under the big lights at the pool."
TitMainTitle: Ammon Center swimming pool encircled with chain link fence, wooden bench, and row houses in background, seen from above
